rndInactiveArpTimeOut.name: rndInactiveArpTimeOut
rndInactiveArpTimeOut.description: This variable defines the maximum time period that can pass between ARP requests concerning an entry in the ARP table. After this time period, the entry is deleted from the table.

rndErrorSeverity.description: The severity type of the enterprise-specific trap sent to the Network Management Station by the switch001 managed device.

rndBrgLicense.name: rndBrgLicense
rndBrgLicense.description: This parameter is used for entering a s/w license number for a device. A separate license number is supplied for each device.

rndCommunityEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rndCommunityMngStationAddr.name: rndCommunityMngStationAddr
rndCommunityMngStationAddr.description: The management station that will be allowed to communicate with the agent IP address

rndCommunityString.name: rndCommunityString
rndCommunityString.description: The community string with which the management station will communicate with the agent

rndCommunityAccess.name: rndCommunityAccess
rndCommunityAccess.description: The allowed access to this management station

rndCommunityTrapsEnable.name: rndCommunityTrapsEnable
rndCommunityTrapsEnable.description: Should the agent send traps to the management station, and what version is required

rndCommunityStatus.name: rndCommunityStatus
rndCommunityStatus.description: The status of this entry. If the status is invalid the community entry will be deleted

rndCommunityPortSecurity.name: rndCommunityPortSecurity
rndCommunityPortSecurity.description: If enabled the device will only receive SNMP messages from the port, through which this NMS is reachable from the device.

rndCommunityTrapDestPort.name: rndCommunityTrapDestPort
rndCommunityTrapDestPort.description: The transport protocol (usually UDP) port to which traps to the management station represebted by this entry will be sent. The default is the well-known IANA assigned port number for SNMP traps. This object is relevant only if rndCommunityTrapsEnable has a value different from trapsDisable.

rlMridEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlMridConnection.description: The router instance connecting the NMS who accessed the agent through the community table entry corresponding to the keys of this entry.

rlManagedMrid.name: rlManagedMrid
rlManagedMrid.description: The router instance currently managed by the NMS who accessed the agent through the community table entry corresponding to the keys of this entry

rndManagedDate.description: The date will be sent in the format ddmmyy

genGroupHWVersion.description: Defines the HW version of the product.

genGroupConfigurationSymbol.name: genGroupConfigurationSymbol
genGroupConfigurationSymbol.description: Defines the Configuration Symbol attached to any hardware module manufactured by LANNET. One single character A..Z defines the CS version.

genGroupHWStatus.name: genGroupHWStatus
genGroupHWStatus.description: This attribute describes the status of the group hardware as detected by the sensors software.

rndBasePhysicalAddress.name: rndBasePhysicalAddress
rndBasePhysicalAddress.description: The Base physical (MAC) address of the device.

rndActiveSoftwareFileTable.name: rndActiveSoftwareFileTable
rndActiveSoftwareFileTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the active software file of the requested unit.

rndActiveSoftwareFileEntry.name: rndActiveSoftwareFileEntry
rndActiveSoftwareFileEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the rndActiveSoftwareFileTable.

rndUnitNumber.name: rndUnitNumber
rndUnitNumber.description: The unit number (for stackable devices) or 1 for 'stand alone' device.

rndActiveSoftwareFile.name: rndActiveSoftwareFile
rndActiveSoftwareFile.description: Indicates the current active software file, image1 or image2.

rndActiveSoftwareFileAfterReset.name: rndActiveSoftwareFileAfterReset
rndActiveSoftwareFileAfterReset.description: Indicates the software file that will be active after reset (image1 or image2). If an error occurred in the download process, resulting in the corruption of the single software file, The value 'invalidImage' will be returned. This value can not be set by the user.

rlResetStatus.name: rlResetStatus
rlResetStatus.description: A bit mask that specifies system status before reset action is preformed. Reset is prohibited in stackable products if the images selected after reboot are not of the same release version in ALL stack units. Downgrade status specifies that there are some actions to be preformed on the CDB file before reset is preformed. 0x0 - OK 0x1 - noStackIntegrity 0x2 - downgrade

rndImageSize.name: rndImageSize
rndImageSize.description: Max number of sectors currently allocated for image(s).

rndBackupConfigurationEnabled.name: rndBackupConfigurationEnabled
rndBackupConfigurationEnabled.description: Specifies whether the device supports backup-config parameters in lcli commands.

rndImageInfoTable.name: rndImageInfoTable
rndImageInfoTable.description: The table contains information about images.

rndStackUnitNumber.name: rndStackUnitNumber
rndStackUnitNumber.description: The unit number (for stackable devices) or 1 for 'stand alone' device.

rndImage1Name.name: rndImage1Name
rndImage1Name.description: Indicates the file name of image-1 in the system.

rndImage2Name.name: rndImage2Name
rndImage2Name.description: Indicates the file name of image-2 (if present) in the system.If image-2 is not present show 'no info' text

rndImage1Version.name: rndImage1Version
rndImage1Version.description: Indicates the version of image-1 in the system.

rndImage2Version.name: rndImage2Version
rndImage2Version.description: Indicates the version of image-2 (if present) in the system.If image-2 is not present show 'no info' text

rndImage1Date.name: rndImage1Date
rndImage1Date.description: Indicates the compilation date of image-1 in the system.

rndImage2Date.name: rndImage2Date
rndImage2Date.description: Indicates the compilation date of image-2 (if present) in the system.If image-2 is not present show 'no info' text

rndImage1Time.name: rndImage1Time
rndImage1Time.description: Indicates the compilation time of image-1 in the system.

rndImage2Time.name: rndImage2Time
rndImage2Time.description: Indicates the compilation time of image-2 (if present) in the system.If image-2 is not present show 'no info' text

rndImage1Description.name: rndImage1Description
rndImage1Description.description: Indicates the description of image-1 in the system.

rndImage2Description.name: rndImage2Description
rndImage2Description.description: Indicates the description of image-2 in the system.
